The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Sunday, December 19, 2004 

 Train runs over teen near Park Circus

 OUR BUREAU 

 Calcutta, Dec. 18: A teenager was killed and four persons, including a police constable, were seriously injured in separate accidents across the city. 

 Thirteen-year-old Sahabuddin, a resident of Park Circus, was killed after he was run over by a Sealdah-bound EMU at 11.05 am just outside Park Circus station. 

 The Government Railway Police personnel took hours to remove the corpse, triggering anger among the people. Officials at the GRP station at Sealdah said the body was finally taken away at 2 pm. 

 Mohan Kumar Sadhukhan, 48, a police constable posted with the headquarters of Calcutta Police?s traffic guard, was hit by a matador while on duty near Andrews Church in the Hare Street police station area. He has been admitted to Calcutta Medical Research Institute, where his condition is said to be serious. 

 Police said the matador was travelling in the wrong direction on a one-way road. When Sadhukhan tried to stop the vehicle, the driver did not brake and slammed into the constable. The driver fled but the vehicle was seized. 

 In another incident, three passengers were injured when a Kidderpore-bound private bus rammed into the divider on the road while trying to overtake another vehicle. Officials of South Port police station said the injured were admitted to SSKM hospital in a serious condition. 

 Police officials said about 24 passengers were in the bus at the time of the mishap. 

Salt Lake suicide

 Sukanya Reddy, 48, a resident of CE block, hanged herself in her bedroom on Friday night. Police said the door was locked from inside and the neighbours saw the body on Saturday morning.




